House Resolution 935
By: Representative Taylor of the 92nd
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing Bald Rock Baptist Church and congratulating Pastor Christopher M. Shipp on
2 the occasion of his 28th pastoral anniversary; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Bald Rock Baptist Church was established in approximately 1861, as Rockdale
4 County's first African American Congregation; and
5 WHEREAS, the plantation where Bald Rock Baptist Church was located served as a place
6 for slaves to worship; and
7 WHEREAS, the original Bald Rock Baptist Church structure is located on Costley Mill Road
8 at the Georgia International Horse Park, and is now a historic site; and
9 WHEREAS, the current Bald Rock Baptist Church building was built in 1994, by its
10 members and under the guidance of the late Reverend Jack Maultsby and the Board of
11 Deacons; and
12 WHEREAS, Pastor Christopher M. Shipp became Shepherd of Bald Rock Baptist Church
13 in February of 1997; and
