14 WHEREAS, his vision and direction have helped Bald Rock Baptist Church grow in size and
15 influence, uplifting the community like the light of Bethlehem and serving as a spiritual
16 leader and place for fellowship; and
17 WHEREAS, whether the task is preparing a sermon, visiting the sick, counseling the
18 troubled, baptizing a new believer, or acting as a theologian, educator, administrator, or
19 humanitarian, Pastor Christopher M. Shipp serves as a shining example of God's righteous
20 path; and
21 WHEREAS, the unmatched spiritual assistance offered by Pastor Christopher M. Shipp is
22 a source of strength and direction for persons in all walks of life.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
24 the members of this body recognize Bald Rock Baptist Church for its historicall presance in
25 Rockdale County, congratulate Pastor Christopher M. Shipp on the occasion of his 28th
26 pastoral anniversary, and extend best wishes for many more years of successful fellowship
27 and leadership.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to Pastor
30 Christopher M. Shipp and Bald Rock Baptist Church.
